item.title: Project
item.dc:creator: trmit
item.content:encoded:
Unreal Engine 4: Project Idea

Project Overview:

Development of a game using the Unreal Engine software. The game is a fantasy medieval action role-playing game with a focus on making the game difficult for the player keeping the player on their toes. 

The Motivation Behind This Project:

The motivation for this project is due to my own personal interest in gaming and wanting to one day make a game of my own. This will also enhance my skills with 'Unreal Engine’ and hopefully teach me a little bit about C++ coding. Also, to note it is evident from the sales of a similar game 'Dark Souls' from the same genre that this type of game is popular. Between the 4 games in the series 25 million copies were sold worldwide. 

Description Of The Project:

This project is a fantasy medieval based game being made in 'Unreal Engine 4'. Due to my lack of knowledge of C++ I would be learning from tutorials and taking advantage of the blueprints that are accessible in the Engine.

The game is based on a hero, who must defeat the 'Evil King' to rid the land of a curse that has be bestowed upon them, that has turned majority of the world into stone.

The user may choose their own fate in terms of direction they want to travel and in which ever order they would like. The part of the games difficulty will scale depending the level of the character and their current progression in the game. However, to complete the game, they must collect the 4 keys hidden behind bosses from 4 different regions in the game. Once they battle to get these keys, they must open the gates to the Evil King's Castle. Defeating the final boss will reverse the curse he has put on the folk of the land.

This game will be more focused on challenging the players at all moments from start to finish with added difficult as you progress. To battle this difficulty, the user must upgrade their armour, skills and equipment. The player may collect items, earn experience and gold from chests and enemies from around the world. When things get really difficult, Co-op mode may be the best choice for the player. Focusing on building heroes that benefit each other will help the player prosper. When Co-oping difficulty will be risen depending on both levels of the characters in the game. Co-op will be available start to finish so that players don't need to play alone.

The player also has a choice of what class they would prefer to be at the start of the game.

Class Types:
Knight - A generic 1 handed melee and shield wielding hero with great skills with wielding their sword and a great defence.
Brute - A hero who loves 2 handed melee weapons with the focus on strength and annihilating their opponent.
Mage - A hero that focuses on magic and potions to guide them through the game
Summoner - A hero with magical capabilities, however, relies heavily on minions the user can summon to fight their battles for them.
Archer - A hero that focuses on the use of their bow and arrow from range.

Even though you choose one of these Starting Class types, you will only receive the base stats and weaponry they would start with. You may choose to mix and match these classes later or completely change your class throughout your travels.

Unreal Engine 4: Project Idea

Tools and Technologies Needed For This Project:

The Engine we will use to build this game is called the 'Unreal Engine 4’. This Engine is used by a lot of the top AAA games that have come out in the past and will in the future. Some good examples of AAA titles that have used this engine are, ‘Batman Arkham Asylum’, ‘Borderlands 3’ and ‘Fortnite’. (Wiki). The great thing about this Engine is that it's free until your game is developed and making over 3,000 USD quarterly, which is great for a amateur like myself. The software uses a predominantly C++ format when coding. Unreal, also offers a platform to find and/or buy models, game sounds and more for your project (List of Unreal Engine games, 2020).

Skills Required For This Project:

The skills required to program in the most optimal way is knowing C++. However, Unreal Engine does offer a lot of blueprints so that people with little to no prior coding knowledge may still be able to use their software. The blueprints are premade blocks of code that you can add to objects to make interactions. Even with minimal knowledge on coding and using the program, 'Unreal Engine' has been out for a long time so there are plenty of guides and tutorials online to help new users (Denham, n.d.).

Outcome Of This Project:

If this project is successful, hopefully a well-polished game will be made from it. Even though the aim is to make a game, there are still other outcomes from this project. You get to learn the 'Unreal Engine' software, and how to use at least the basics of it and some other advanced tools. You may even learn a bit of C++ coding through watching online tutorials and guides on how to make certain things in the game. The development of this game could help make future game development of games faster and easier due to prior knowledge.

item.dc:creator: trmit
item.content:encoded:
What Career In I.T Would I Like To Pursue?

What Would My Ideal Job Be In I.T?

My ideal job in I.T would be working in Cyber Security, more specifically Cyber Security Analysis.
An example of this position can be found on Seek and can be accessed here.

Description Of This Position:

A 'Cyber Security Analyst' is required to uphold Cyber Security Standards and make sure they are met throughout the whole company. Defend against and simulate cyber attacks to determine ways to protect the company against them. Work with other I.T departments and make sure that Cyber Security Standards are met.

What Interests You About This Position?

Cyber Security has always interested me, as I love problem solving, keeping everything up to the required standard and managing things.

What Does The Position Require?

To succeed in getting this position I'll need need to have the following experience, knowledge, and traits:

  • Analytical mindset.
  • Ability to work in a team.
  • Able to communicate with stakeholders that are both technical and non-technical.
  • Knowledge of security standards and required frameworks; ISO 27001, PSPF, ISM, VPDSF.
  • Provide general security operations.
  • Knowledge on Cloud based software.
  • Knowledge on managing vulnerability and SIEM tools.
  • Required to have 1 or more certifications; CISSP, CEH, CISSP, CEH, ISO 27001, and CompTia Security+
  • 5 years previous experience in Information Security Roles.

What Qualifications Do You Currently Have For The Position?

Unfortunately I currently have no qualifications for this position, however, one day I hope to obtain the qualification and experience to be able to get a position like this in the future.

item.title: About
item.dc:creator: trmit
item.content:encoded:
Tyson Carroll, previously a Science student at RMIT, now adventuring through the ropes of I.T.

Contact Info:
Name: Tyson Carroll
Student Number: S3660241
Email: s3660241@student.rmit.edu.au

Who Am I?

Hello, my name is Tyson and welcome to my website about me. I am Australian born, however, my dad’s side of the family is from Turkey. Unfortunately, I can not speak any other languages other than English, but I do strive to eventually learn other languages like Mandarin to help me with future endeavors and travels. Before studying Information Technology (I.T), I studied Science for 2 years at RMIT. I discontinued my study of Science to dabble and hopefully seek a career in I.T.

Interests?

Basketball

Gaming

Computers

Video Editing

What Interests Me About I.T?

I am always been interested in I.T ever since I got my first computer at the age of around 10 years old. I always loved playing games on my computer ever since then and now I want to learn more about what is behind the scene of computer software, cyber-security and the making of video games. Not only did this event spark my interest in the field of I.T, however, the recent building of a few computers for my friends, and myself re-lit this interest for I.T that I had when I was younger.

Why RMIT?

I chose RMIT as my place of study for I.T as I knew it had an amazing environment from my previous studies of Science at this University. However, before I.T and Science, I chose RMIT because I knew it was a highly reputable University, so I knew it would be a good decision to pick this as one of my preferred Universities of choice.

What do you expect to learn from your studies at RMIT?

I hope to learn the fundamentals of I.T to help further my knowledge in the area to hopefully specialise in a specific field or multiple fields. The topics I am most interested about is Cyber-Security and Game development.

item.title: Introduce Yourself (Example Post)
item.dc:creator: trmit
item.content:encoded:
This is an example post, originally published as part of Blogging University. Enroll in one of our ten programs, and start your blog right.

You’re going to publish a post today. Don’t worry about how your blog looks. Don’t worry if you haven’t given it a name yet, or you’re feeling overwhelmed. Just click the “New Post” button, and tell us why you’re here.

Why do this?

  • Because it gives new readers context. What are you about? Why should they read your blog?
  • Because it will help you focus your own ideas about your blog and what you’d like to do with it.

The post can be short or long, a personal intro to your life or a bloggy mission statement, a manifesto for the future or a simple outline of your the types of things you hope to publish.

To help you get started, here are a few questions:

  • Why are you blogging publicly, rather than keeping a personal journal?
  • What topics do you think you’ll write about?
  • Who would you love to connect with via your blog?
  • If you blog successfully throughout the next year, what would you hope to have accomplished?

You’re not locked into any of this; one of the wonderful things about blogs is how they constantly evolve as we learn, grow, and interact with one another — but it’s good to know where and why you started, and articulating your goals may just give you a few other post ideas.

Can’t think how to get started? Just write the first thing that pops into your head. Anne Lamott, author of a book on writing we love, says that you need to give yourself permission to write a “crappy first draft”. Anne makes a great point — just start writing, and worry about editing it later.

When you’re ready to publish, give your post three to five tags that describe your blog’s focus — writing, photography, fiction, parenting, food, cars, movies, sports, whatever. These tags will help others who care about your topics find you in the Reader. Make sure one of the tags is “zerotohero,” so other new bloggers can find you, too.

My Thoughts On Personality Tests:

The results of these tests don’t mean much to me personally, as I feel the results can change depending on the persons mood as we can change our perception on ourselves. I believe these tests won’t affect my ability to work in a group as I can adapt to the situation depending on the role that is required to be filled and what is needed of me by other members in a group. I can see how these tests can help forming a team with others, however, I don’t think we should be heavily reliant on these types of tests when forming groups.
